to the luscious Bobbi Dylan.</i>

464
00:36:42,284 --> 00:36:44,953
- All right!
- Bobbi!

465
00:37:07,476 --> 00:37:09,561
<i>Her dream had come true.</i>

466
00:37:10,812 --> 00:37:12,814
<i>She was a folk singer.</i>

467
00:37:22,074 --> 00:37:24,326
Come on, baby. Shake it up.
Shake it up, now.

468
00:37:24,409 --> 00:37:25,911
Hey, buddy, get her a harmonica.

469
00:37:29,665 --> 00:37:31,708
Hey, honey, this ain't <i>Captain Kangaroo.</i>

470
00:37:31,833 --> 00:37:34,378
Hey, honey, I got something here for you.

471
00:37:35,420 --> 00:37:39,174
- God damn it!
- Hey! Hey! Stupid jerk!

472
00:37:39,258 --> 00:37:41,718
I'm singing a song here.

473
00:37:44,054 --> 00:37:46,515
Polly, get out here!

474
00:37:46,556 --> 00:37:48,383
- Shut up, there!
- Don't be so shy, honey.

475
00:37:48,393 --> 00:37:49,936
Oh, shut up!

476
00:37:52,562 --> 00:37:55,357
Forrest, what are you doing here?

477
00:37:55,399 --> 00:37:57,109
- What are you doing?
- Hey!

478
00:37:57,192 --> 00:37:58,568
- Come on.
- What are you doing?

479
00:37:58,694 --> 00:38:00,696
Forrest, let me down!

480
00:38:06,535 --> 00:38:08,453
You can't keep doing this, Forrest.

481
00:38:08,537 --> 00:38:10,664
You can't keep trying
to rescue me all the time.

482
00:38:10,706 --> 00:38:14,793
- They was trying to grab you.
- A lot of people try to grab me.

483
00:38:15,711 --> 00:38:18,880
Just... You can't keep
doing this all the time.

484
00:38:19,381 --> 00:38:22,301
I can't help it. I love you.

485
00:38:23,260 --> 00:38:26,763
Forrest, you don't know what love is.

486
00:38:34,062 --> 00:38:37,065
You remember that time
we prayed, Forrest?

487
00:38:37,941 --> 00:38:42,446
We prayed for God to turn me
into a bird so I could fly far, far away?

488
00:38:44,406 --> 00:38:45,782
Yes, I do.

489
00:38:49,745 --> 00:38:52,581
You think I could fly off this bridge?

490
00:38:59,254 --> 00:39:01,423
What do you mean, Jenny?

491
00:39:05,302 --> 00:39:06,803
Nothing.

492
00:39:09,765 --> 00:39:11,808
I gotta get out of here.

493
00:39:14,102 --> 00:39:15,228
Wait, Jenny...

494
00:39:15,270 --> 00:39:19,775
Forrest, you stay away from me, okay?
You just stay away from me, please.

495
00:39:19,816 --> 00:39:21,109
Can I have a ride?

496
00:39:21,193 --> 00:39:22,778
- Where you going?
- I don't care.

497
00:39:22,819 --> 00:39:24,196
Get in the truck.

498
00:39:24,279 --> 00:39:26,114
So, bye-bye, Jenny.

499
00:39:28,617 --> 00:39:30,952
They sending me to Vietnam.

500
00:39:33,705 --> 00:39:36,124
It's this whole other country.

501
00:39:38,627 --> 00:39:40,629
Just hang on a minute.

502
00:39:42,047 --> 00:39:45,133
Listen, you promise me something, okay?

503
00:39:45,175 --> 00:39:48,512
Just, if you're ever in trouble,
don't try to be brave. You just run, okay?

504
00:39:48,637 --> 00:39:50,222
Just run away.

505
00:39:51,473 --> 00:39:52,808
Okay.

506
00:39:57,687 --> 00:39:59,022
Jenny.

507
00:40:00,899 --> 00:40:03,193
I'll write you all the time.

508
00:40:12,327 --> 00:40:15,330
<i>And just like that, she was gone.</i>

509
00:40:31,430 --> 00:40:34,766
You come back safe to me, do you hear?

510
00:41:18,059 --> 00:41:22,063
<i>Now, they told us that Vietnam
was gonna be very different</i>

511
00:41:22,105 --> 00:41:24,983
<i>from the United States of America.</i>

512
00:41:25,066 --> 00:41:30,113
<i>And except for all the beer cans
and the barbecue, it was.</i>

513
00:41:40,248 --> 00:41:43,335
Hey, I bet there's shrimp
all in these waters.

514
00:41:43,418 --> 00:41:46,588
They tell me these Vietnams
is good shrimpers.

515
00:41:46,671 --> 00:41:50,258
You know, after we win this war,
and we take over everything,

516
00:41:50,300 --> 00:41:51,561
we can get American shrimpers

517
00:41:51,593 --> 00:41:53,376
to come out here and shrimp these waters.

518
00:41:53,428 --> 00:41:54,994
We'll just shrimp all the time, man.

519
00:41:55,096 --> 00:41:58,266
So much shrimp, why,
you wouldn't believe it.

520
00:41:58,934 --> 00:42:00,894
You must be my FNGs.

521
00:42:00,936 --> 00:42:02,241
- Morning, sir!
- Morning, sir!

522
00:42:02,270 --> 00:42:04,940
Get your hands down! Do not salute me.

523
00:42:04,981 --> 00:42:07,108
There's goddamn snipers
all around this area

524
00:42:07,192 --> 00:42:10,028
who would love to grease an officer.

525
00:42:10,111 --> 00:42:13,615
I'm Lieutenant Dan Taylor.
Welcome to Fourth Platoon.

526
00:42:14,491 --> 00:42:16,952
What's wrong with your lip?

527
00:42:16,993 --> 00:42:19,371
I was born with big gums, sir.

528
00:42:19,454 --> 00:42:24,167
Yeah, well, you better tuck that in.
Gonna get that caught on a trip wire.

529
00:42:25,335 --> 00:42:26,770
Where you boys from in the world?

530
00:42:26,795 --> 00:42:29,172
- Alabama, sir!
- Alabama, sir!

531
00:42:29,881 --> 00:42:31,383
You twins?

532
00:42:33,468 --> 00:42:35,887
No, we are not relations, sir.

533
00:42:38,139 --> 00:42:41,059
Look, it's pretty basic here.

534
00:42:41,851 --> 00:42:44,312
If you stick with me
and learn from the guys

535
00:42:44,396 --> 00:42:47,107
who've been in country a while,
you'll be all right.

536
00:42:47,148 --> 00:42:49,109
There is one item of GI gear

537
00:42:49,150 --> 00:42:53,321
that can be the difference between
a live grunt and a dead grunt.

538
00:42:53,655 --> 00:42:56,825
Socks. Cushion sole, OD green.

539
00:42:56,908 --> 00:42:58,201
Try and keep your feet dry.

540
00:42:58,326 --> 00:43:00,500
When we're out humping,
I want you boys to remember

541
00:43:00,510 --> 00:43:02,330
to change your socks whenever we stop.

542
00:43:02,372 --> 00:43:05,333
The Mekong will eat a grunt's feet
right off his legs.

543
00:43:05,417 --> 00:43:07,711
Sergeant Sims, God damn it,

544
00:43:07,836 --> 00:43:09,327
where is that sling rope
I told you to order?

545
00:43:09,337 --> 00:43:11,256
I put in the requisitions at Battalion.

546
00:43:11,339 --> 00:43:14,035
Yeah, yeah, yeah, well,
you call those sons of bitches again...

547
00:43:14,045 --> 00:43:18,966
<i>Lieutenant Dan sure knew his stuff.
I felt real lucky he was my lieutenant.</i>

548
00:43:19,097 --> 00:43:22,559
<i>He was from a long,
great military tradition.</i>

549
00:43:22,767 --> 00:43:25,854
<i>Somebody in his family
had fought and died</i>

550
00:43:26,855 --> 00:43:31,109
<i>in every single American war.</i>

551
00:43:32,027 --> 00:43:34,332
- God damn it, kick some ass!
- I'm on it, Lieutenant.

552
00:43:34,342 --> 00:43:35,238
Get on it!

553
00:43:35,363 --> 00:43:38,700
<i>I guess you could say he had
a lot to live up to.</i>

554
00:43:40,410 --> 00:43:45,248
So, you boys are from Arkansas, huh?
Well, I've been through there.

555
00:43:45,373 --> 00:43:47,542
Little Rock's a fine town.

556
00:43:48,209 --> 00:43:51,796
Now, go shake down your gear,
see the platoon sergeant,

557
00:43:51,880 --> 00:43:54,382
draw what you need for the field.

558
00:43:54,424 --> 00:43:58,386
If you boys are hungry,
we got steaks burning right over here.

559
00:43:58,470 --> 00:44:01,389
Two standing orders in this platoon:

560
00:44:01,431 --> 00:44:04,100
one, take good care of your feet,

561
00:44:04,225 --> 00:44:09,272
two, try not to do anything stupid,
like getting yourself killed.

562
00:44:15,737 --> 00:44:17,822
I sure hope I don't let him down.

563
00:44:29,417 --> 00:44:34,339
<i>I got to see a lot of the countryside.
We would take these real long walks.</i>

564
00:44:42,806 --> 00:44:46,935
<i>And we were always looking
for this guy named Charlie.</i>

565
00:44:54,776 --> 00:44:57,028
- Hold it up!
- Hold up, boys!

566
00:44:59,864 --> 00:45:02,200
<i>It wasn't always fun.</i>

567
00:45:02,283 --> 00:45:06,621
<i>Lieutenant Dan was always getting
these funny feelings about a rock,</i>

568
00:45:06,663 --> 00:45:11,793
<i>or a trail, or the road,
so he'd tell us to get down, shut up...</i>

569
00:45:11,835 --> 00:45:13,837
Get down! Shut up!

570
00:45:14,796 --> 00:45:16,256
<i>...so we did.</i>

571
00:45:33,815 --> 00:45:35,984
<i>Now, I don't know much about anything,</i>

572
00:45:36,067 --> 00:45:39,904
<i>but I think some of America's
best young men served in this war.</i>

573
00:45:39,988 --> 00:45:42,699
<i>There was Dallas, from Phoenix,</i>

574
00:45:44,409 --> 00:45:47,203
<i>Cleveland, he was from Detroit.</i>

575
00:45:47,328 --> 00:45:49,706
Hey, Tex. Hey, Tex.

576
00:45:49,831 --> 00:45:52,000
Man, what the hell's going on?

577
00:45:52,083 --> 00:45:56,421
<i>And Tex was... Well, I don't remember
where Tex come from.</i>

578
00:45:56,504 --> 00:45:58,047
Nothing.

579
00:46:02,177 --> 00:46:04,679
Fourth Platoon, on your feet.

580
00:46:04,763 --> 00:46:08,516
Still got 10 klicks to go to that river.
Move out.

581
00:46:08,558 --> 00:46:10,351
Come on, move out.

582
00:46:12,395 --> 00:46:14,856
Step it up. Look alive out there.

583
00:46:14,898 --> 00:46:19,235
<i>The good thing about Vietnam
is there was always some place to go.</i>

584
00:46:19,360 --> 00:46:20,737
Fire in the hole!

585
00:46:24,199 --> 00:46:26,534
Gump, check out that hole.

586
00:46:26,618 --> 00:46:29,621
<i>And there was always something to do.</i>

587
00:46:29,704 --> 00:46:32,874
- Mount them up.
- Spread out! Cover his back.

588
00:46:37,921 --> 00:46:43,551
<i>One day, it started raining,
and it didn't quit for four months.</i>

589
00:46:44,552 --> 00:46:47,430
<i>We'd been through
every kind of rain there is:</i>

590
00:46:47,555 --> 00:46:50,099
<i>little bitty stinging rain,</i>

591
00:46:50,809 --> 00:46:53,478
<i>and big old fat rain,</i>

592
00:46:53,937 --> 00:46:56,648
<i>rain that flew in sideways.</i>

593
00:46:56,731 --> 00:47:00,777
<i>And sometimes, rain even seemed
to come straight up from underneath.</i>

594
00:47:02,570 --> 00:47:04,948
<i>Shoot, it even rained at night.</i>

595
00:47:05,990 --> 00:47:08,451
- Hey, Forrest.
- Hey, Bubba.

596
00:47:08,576 --> 00:47:11,913
I'm gonna lean up against you.
You just lean right back against me.

597
00:47:11,955 --> 00:47:15,792
This way, we don't have to sleep
with our heads in the mud.

598
00:47:16,751 --> 00:47:20,255
You know why we a good partnership,
Forrest?

599
00:47:20,296 --> 00:47:22,799
'Cause we be watching out
for one another,

600
00:47:22,924 --> 00:47:24,801
like brothers and stuff.

601
00:47:26,761 --> 00:47:30,431
Hey, Forrest, there's something
I've been thinking about.

602
00:47:30,515 --> 00:47:33,518
I got a very important question
to ask you.

603
00:47:35,144 --> 00:47:39,107
How would you like to go
into the shrimping business with me?

604
00:47:40,275 --> 00:47:41,943
Okay.

605
00:47:41,985 --> 00:47:45,446
Man, I tell you what,
I got it all figured out, too.

606
00:47:45,530 --> 00:47:48,324
So many pounds of shrimp
to pay off the boat,

607
00:47:48,449 --> 00:47:51,786
so many pounds for gas,
we can just live right on the boat.

608
00:47:51,828 --> 00:47:54,122
We ain't got to pay no rent.

609
00:47:54,205 --> 00:47:56,336
I'll be the captain,
we can just work it together,

610
00:47:56,374 --> 00:48:00,628
split everything right down the middle.
Man, I'm telling you, 50-50.

611
00:48:00,712 --> 00:48:04,299
And, hey, Forrest,
all the shrimp you can eat.

612
00:48:05,842 --> 00:48:07,635
That's a fine idea.

613
00:48:08,720 --> 00:48:10,847
<i>Bubba did have a fine idea.</i>

614
00:48:14,642 --> 00:48:17,729
<i>I even wrote Jenny
and told her all about it.</i>

615
00:48:18,521 --> 00:48:21,733
<i>I sent her letters,
not every day, but almost.</i>

616
00:48:21,816 --> 00:48:26,821
<i>I told her what I was doing
and asked her what she was doing,</i>

617
00:48:26,905 --> 00:48:29,657
<i>and told her
how I thought about her always,</i>

618
00:48:30,992 --> 00:48:33,995
<i>and how I was looking forward
to getting a letter from her</i>

619
00:48:34,037 --> 00:48:36,539
<i>just as soon as she had the time.</i>

620
00:48:38,416 --> 00:48:40,919
<i>I'd always let her know that I was okay.</i>

621
00:48:42,211 --> 00:48:47,383
<i>Then, I'd sign each letter,
"Love, Forrest Gump."</i>

622
00:49:02,231 --> 00:49:06,027
<i>This one day, we was out walking,
like always,</i>

623
00:49:06,069 --> 00:49:09,030
<i>and then, just like that,</i>

624
00:49:09,948 --> 00:49:13,368
<i>somebody turned off the rain
and the sun come out.</i>

625
00:49:16,371 --> 00:49:18,206
Ambush!

626
00:49:18,706 --> 00:49:20,083
Take cover!

627
00:49:23,711 --> 00:49:24,879
Get down!

628
00:49:24,963 --> 00:49:26,422
Get the sixty!

629
00:49:29,592 --> 00:49:31,719
Get that pig up here, God damn it!

630
00:49:31,761 --> 00:49:33,888
Forrest, you okay?

631
00:49:37,100 --> 00:49:39,727
Strongarm! Strongarm!
Be advised, Strongarm!

632
00:49:40,269 --> 00:49:42,730
Medic, we got a man down!

633
00:49:42,772 --> 00:49:45,733
Strongarm, this is Leg Lima 6, over!

634
00:49:46,442 --> 00:49:49,779
Roger, Strongarm, be advised
we have incoming from the tree line

635
00:49:49,904 --> 00:49:53,408
at points blue plus two.
AKs and rockets...

636
00:49:54,075 --> 00:49:55,868
Misfire! Misfire!

637
00:49:58,246 --> 00:50:00,248
God damn it! Mac!

638
00:50:01,207 --> 00:50:04,627
Get that thing...
Fuck it, get it in the tree line!

639
00:50:05,586 --> 00:50:06,754
Jesus!

640
00:50:06,879 --> 00:50:09,090
My unit is down hard and hurting!

641
00:50:09,215 --> 00:50:12,760
Six are pulling back to Blue Line,
Leg Lima 6 out.

642
00:50:13,553 --> 00:50:15,555
Pull back! Pull back!

643
00:50:15,596 --> 00:50:17,724
Run! Run, Forrest!

644
00:50:17,807 --> 00:50:20,143
- Pull back!
- Forrest, Forrest!

645
00:50:20,268 --> 00:50:22,895
Run, man! Run!

646
00:50:22,937 --> 00:50:24,731
Pull back! Run!

647
00:50:26,566 --> 00:50:28,776
Run, God damn it, run!

648
00:50:49,964 --> 00:50:54,594
Medic! Can I get a medic?

649
00:50:54,969 --> 00:50:58,306
<i>I ran and ran, just like Jenny told me to.</i>

650
00:51:01,684 --> 00:51:05,938
<i>I ran so far and so fast
that pretty soon I was all by myself,</i>

651
00:51:05,980 --> 00:51:07,940
<i>which was a bad thing.</i>

652
00:51:08,483 --> 00:51:10,026
Bubba!

653
00:51:12,153 --> 00:51:15,948
<i>Bubba was my best good friend.
I had to make sure that he was okay.</i>

654
00:51:19,660 --> 00:51:21,704
Any friendlies out there?

655
00:51:22,663 --> 00:51:24,832
Yeah, I've got three over here.

656
00:51:25,458 --> 00:51:27,460
Where the hell are you?

657
00:51:28,044 --> 00:51:29,378
Bubba?

658
00:51:30,463 --> 00:51:33,174
<i>And on my way back to find Bubba,</i>

659
00:51:33,299 --> 00:51:36,135
<i>well, there was this boy
laying on the ground.</i>

660
00:51:36,177 --> 00:51:37,386
Tex!

661
00:51:39,472 --> 00:51:40,515
Okay.

662
00:51:40,556 --> 00:51:43,033
<i>I couldn't just let him
lay there all alone,</i>

663
00:51:43,044 --> 00:51:44,529
<i>scared the way he was,</i>

664
00:51:44,644 --> 00:51:48,523
<i>so I grabbed him up
and run him out of there.</i>

665
00:52:03,663 --> 00:52:06,082
<i>And every time I went back
looking for Bubba,</i>

666
00:52:06,207 --> 00:52:09,710
<i>somebody else was saying,
"Help me, Forrest. Help me."</i>

667
00:52:17,385 --> 00:52:19,262
Can't hear... Can't hear...

668
00:52:21,556 --> 00:52:22,890
No sweat, man. Just lay back.

669
00:52:22,932 --> 00:52:25,434
You'll be okay. You'll be okay.

670
00:52:27,436 --> 00:52:30,523
<i>I started to get scared
that I might never find Bubba.</i>

671
00:52:30,565 --> 00:52:31,858
<i>...over.</i>

672
00:52:31,899 --> 00:52:35,236
Roger, Strongarm,
I know my position is danger close.

673
00:52:35,278 --> 00:52:37,113
We got Charlie all over this area.

674
00:52:37,238 --> 00:52:39,574
I gotta have those fast movers
in here now. Over.

675
00:52:39,615 --> 00:52:43,035
<i>- Six, Strongarm, we want...</i>
- Lieutenant Dan, Coleman's dead!

676
00:52:43,077 --> 00:52:44,287
I know he's dead!

677
00:52:44,412 --> 00:52:47,248
My whole goddamn platoon is wiped out!

678
00:52:47,373 --> 00:52:49,069
<i>- Leg Lima 6, Leg Lima 6.</i>
- God damn it!

679
00:52:49,079 --> 00:52:51,544
<i>- Copy this transmission. Over.</i>
- What are you doing?

680
00:52:51,586 --> 00:52:54,922
Just leave me here! Get away.
Just leave me here! Get out!

681
00:52:55,047 --> 00:52:57,383
<i>Leg Lima 6, Strongarm.
How copy this? Over.</i>

682
00:52:57,425 --> 00:53:00,094
God, I said leave me here, God damn it!

683
00:53:00,136 --> 00:53:03,306
<i>Leg Lima 6, Leg Lima 6,
this is Strongarm, be advised</i>

684
00:53:03,420 --> 00:53:05,464
<i>your fast movers
are inbound at this time, over.</i>

685
00:53:05,474 --> 00:53:08,895
<i>Then, it felt like something
just jumped up and bit me.</i>

686
00:53:09,770 --> 00:53:11,439
Something bit me!

687
00:53:18,321 --> 00:53:20,448
You chink son of a bitch!

688
00:53:22,950 --> 00:53:24,952
I can't leave the platoon.

689
00:53:25,077 --> 00:53:29,999
I told you to leave me there, Gump.
Forget about me. Get yourself out!

690
00:53:30,124 --> 00:53:32,251
Did you hear what I said?

691
00:53:32,960 --> 00:53:34,921
God damn it, put me down!

692
00:53:35,630 --> 00:53:37,673
Get your ass out of here!

693
00:53:40,968 --> 00:53:43,596
I didn't ask you to pull me out of there,
God damn you!

694
00:53:43,638 --> 00:53:45,421
Where the hell do you think you're going?

695
00:53:45,431 --> 00:53:46,231
To get Bubba.

696
00:53:46,307 --> 00:53:50,144
I got an air strike inbound right now.
They're gonna nape the whole area.

697
00:53:50,269 --> 00:53:52,647
Gump, you stay here, God damn it!
