953
01:15:14,594 --> 01:15:16,971
<i>Some years later,
that nice young man from England</i>

954
01:15:17,055 --> 01:15:19,724
<i>was on his way home to see his little boy</i>

955
01:15:19,766 --> 01:15:22,769
<i>and was signing some autographs,</i>

956
01:15:22,894 --> 01:15:26,856
<i>and for no particular reason at all,
somebody shot him.</i>

957
01:15:29,901 --> 01:15:33,738
They gave you
the Congressional Medal of Honor.

958
01:15:35,031 --> 01:15:37,116
Now, that's Lieutenant Dan.

959
01:15:39,911 --> 01:15:41,538
Lieutenant Dan!

960
01:15:41,621 --> 01:15:46,084
They gave you
the Congressional Medal of Honor!

961
01:15:47,961 --> 01:15:49,462
Yes, sir, they surely did.

962
01:15:49,546 --> 01:15:51,548
They gave you,

963
01:15:51,631 --> 01:15:55,802
an imbecile,
a moron who goes on television

964
01:15:55,885 --> 01:16:00,139
and makes a fool out of himself
in front of the whole damn country,

965
01:16:00,807 --> 01:16:03,309
the Congressional Medal of Honor.

966
01:16:04,477 --> 01:16:05,645
Yes, sir.

967
01:16:07,814 --> 01:16:10,650
Well, then, that's just perfect!

968
01:16:12,569 --> 01:16:14,904
Yeah, well,
I just got one thing to say to that.

969
01:16:14,988 --> 01:16:17,240
God damn bless America.

970
01:16:18,157 --> 01:16:19,450
Hey!

971
01:16:21,244 --> 01:16:22,579
Oh, God!

972
01:16:25,081 --> 01:16:27,500
- Oh, God!
- Lieutenant Dan!

973
01:16:28,626 --> 01:16:31,379
<i>Lieutenant Dan said
he was living in a hotel.</i>

974
01:16:31,462 --> 01:16:33,423
<i>And because he didn't have no legs,</i>

975
01:16:33,506 --> 01:16:36,676
<i>he spent most of his time
exercising his arms.</i>

976
01:16:39,554 --> 01:16:42,015
Take a right. Take a right.

977
01:16:44,642 --> 01:16:47,186
Hey! Come on, already!

978
01:16:47,270 --> 01:16:50,064
What do you do here in New York,
Lieutenant Dan?

979
01:16:50,148 --> 01:16:52,692
I'm living off the government tit.

980
01:16:54,319 --> 01:16:55,695
Sucking it dry!

981
01:16:55,778 --> 01:16:57,822
Hey! Hey! Hey! Are you blind?

982
01:16:57,905 --> 01:16:59,645
- I'm walking here!
- Get out of the way!

983
01:16:59,699 --> 01:17:02,285
Get out! Come on, go! Go! Go!

984
01:17:09,334 --> 01:17:13,087
<i>I stayed with Lieutenant Dan
and celebrated the holidays.</i>

985
01:17:17,508 --> 01:17:20,928
<i>You have a great year.
Hurry home and God bless you.</i>

986
01:17:23,931 --> 01:17:26,726
Have you found Jesus yet, Gump?

987
01:17:28,311 --> 01:17:31,981
I didn't know I was supposed to be
looking for him, sir.

988
01:17:38,571 --> 01:17:41,949
That's all these cripples,
down at the VA,

989
01:17:42,033 --> 01:17:44,452
that's all they ever talk about.

990
01:17:45,620 --> 01:17:48,581
Jesus this and Jesus that.

991
01:17:50,041 --> 01:17:52,335
Have I found Jesus?

992
01:17:52,960 --> 01:17:55,963
They even had a priest come
and talk to me.

993
01:17:56,839 --> 01:18:01,511
He said God is listening,
but I have to help myself.

994
01:18:02,887 --> 01:18:05,181
How if I accept Jesus into my heart,

995
01:18:06,182 --> 01:18:09,977
I'll get to walk beside him
in the kingdom of heaven.

996
01:18:10,061 --> 01:18:12,230
Did you hear what I said?

997
01:18:13,272 --> 01:18:17,276
Walk beside him in the kingdom of heaven.

998
01:18:17,360 --> 01:18:20,321
Well, kiss my crippled ass.

999
01:18:20,405 --> 01:18:23,783
God is listening? What a crock of shit.

1000
01:18:27,453 --> 01:18:30,081
I'm going to heaven, Lieutenant Dan.

1001
01:18:31,999 --> 01:18:33,042
Oh?

1002
01:18:37,880 --> 01:18:39,257
Well,

1003
01:18:42,218 --> 01:18:45,596
before you go, why don't you get
your ass down to the corner

1004
01:18:45,680 --> 01:18:48,182
- and get us another bottle of Ripple.
- Yes, sir.

1005
01:18:48,266 --> 01:18:53,396
<i>We are at approximately 45th Street
in New York City at One Astor Plaza.</i>

1006
01:18:53,479 --> 01:18:55,314
<i>This is the site of the old Astor Hotel.</i>

1007
01:18:55,398 --> 01:18:57,608
What the hell is in Bayou La Batre?

1008
01:18:57,692 --> 01:19:00,027
- Shrimping boats.
- Shrimping boats?

1009
01:19:00,111 --> 01:19:02,530
Who gives a shit about shrimping boats?

1010
01:19:02,613 --> 01:19:04,440
I gotta buy me
one of them shrimping boats,

1011
01:19:04,450 --> 01:19:05,700
soon as I have some money.

1012
01:19:05,783 --> 01:19:08,619
I made me a promise to Bubba in Vietnam

1013
01:19:08,703 --> 01:19:11,414
that as soon as the war was over,
we'd go in partners.

1014
01:19:11,497 --> 01:19:14,917
He'd be the captain of the
shrimping boat and I'd be his first mate.

1015
01:19:15,001 --> 01:19:18,463
But now that he's dead,
that means I gotta be the captain.

1016
01:19:18,546 --> 01:19:21,257
- A shrimp boat captain.
- Yes, sir.

1017
01:19:21,340 --> 01:19:24,093
A promise is a promise, Lieutenant Dan.

1018
01:19:25,595 --> 01:19:28,055
Now hear this!

1019
01:19:28,806 --> 01:19:32,643
Private Gump here
is gonna be a shrimp boat captain.

1020
01:19:33,394 --> 01:19:34,812
Well, I tell you what, Gilligan,

1021
01:19:34,896 --> 01:19:37,356
the day that you are
a shrimp boat captain,

1022
01:19:37,440 --> 01:19:40,985
- I will come and be your first mate.
- Okay.

1023
01:19:41,068 --> 01:19:45,406
If you're ever a shrimp boat captain,
that's the day I'm an astronaut.

1024
01:19:45,490 --> 01:19:48,493
Danny, what are you complaining about?

1025
01:19:48,576 --> 01:19:51,162
- What are you doing, hon?
- Mr. Hot Wheels.

1026
01:19:51,245 --> 01:19:54,874
- Who's your friend?
- My name is Forrest, Forrest Gump.

1027
01:19:55,708 --> 01:19:59,921
This is Cunning Carla
and Long-Limbs Lenore.

1028
01:20:01,005 --> 01:20:04,217
So, where you been, baby cakes, huh?
Haven't seen you around lately.

1029
01:20:04,300 --> 01:20:05,833
You know, you should have
been here for Christmas,

1030
01:20:05,843 --> 01:20:07,583
'cause Tommy bought a round on the house

1031
01:20:07,622 --> 01:20:09,231
and gave everybody a turkey sandwich.

1032
01:20:09,241 --> 01:20:11,925
Well, well, I had company.

1033
01:20:12,767 --> 01:20:16,437
Hey, hey! We was just there.
That's at Times Square.

1034
01:20:17,063 --> 01:20:21,192
Don't you just love New Year's?
You get to start all over.

1035
01:20:21,275 --> 01:20:24,570
- Hey, Lenore...
- Everybody gets a second chance.

1036
01:20:24,654 --> 01:20:27,198
<i>It's funny,
but in the middle of all that fun,</i>

1037
01:20:27,281 --> 01:20:29,575
<i>I began to think about Jenny,</i>

1038
01:20:30,493 --> 01:20:34,956
<i>wondering how she was spending
her New Year's night out in California.</i>

1039
01:20:57,562 --> 01:21:01,065
<i>...eight, seven, six, five,</i>

1040
01:21:01,190 --> 01:21:04,652
four, three, two, one!

1041
01:21:04,777 --> 01:21:07,446
Happy New Year!

1042
01:21:23,921 --> 01:21:26,632
Happy New Year, Lieutenant Dan!

1043
01:22:01,918 --> 01:22:05,588
What are you, stupid or something?
What's your problem?

1044
01:22:06,255 --> 01:22:07,673
What's his problem?

1045
01:22:07,757 --> 01:22:10,009
Did you lose your pecker in the war
or something?

1046
01:22:10,092 --> 01:22:12,178
What, is your friend stupid or something?

1047
01:22:12,219 --> 01:22:13,346
What did you say?

1048
01:22:13,387 --> 01:22:15,214
I said, is your friend stupid
or something?

1049
01:22:15,224 --> 01:22:17,058
Hey! Don't call him stupid!

1050
01:22:17,141 --> 01:22:19,101
- Hey, don't you push her!
- You shut up!

1051
01:22:19,185 --> 01:22:21,302
- Don't you ever call him stupid!
- What's the matter, baby?

1052
01:22:21,312 --> 01:22:23,095
- Why are you so upset?
- Just get the hell out of here.

1053
01:22:23,105 --> 01:22:24,263
- Stupid damn...
- Get your goddamn clothes...

1054
01:22:24,273 --> 01:22:25,848
You belong in <i>Ripley's Believe It Or Not!</i>

1055
01:22:25,858 --> 01:22:27,808
- Get the hell out of here!
- You should be in a sideshow!

1056
01:22:27,818 --> 01:22:28,861
Go on! Get out of here!

1057
01:22:28,902 --> 01:22:30,685
Come on, Lenore. We don't need this shit!

1058
01:22:30,695 --> 01:22:32,071
Get out of here!

1059
01:22:33,324 --> 01:22:35,868
- You retard.
- Loser. You freak.

1060
01:22:41,248 --> 01:22:42,458
No, no.

1061
01:23:07,608 --> 01:23:11,570
I'm sorry I ruined your
New Year's Eve party, Lieutenant Dan.

1062
01:23:12,154 --> 01:23:14,448
She tasted like cigarettes.

1063
01:23:30,631 --> 01:23:35,136
<i>I guess Lieutenant Dan figured there's
some things you just can't change.</i>

1064
01:23:35,219 --> 01:23:37,401
<i>He didn't want to be called crippled,</i>

1065
01:23:37,412 --> 01:23:40,359
<i>just like I didn't want
to be called stupid.</i>

1066
01:23:45,855 --> 01:23:47,732
Happy New Year, Gump.

1067
01:23:52,528 --> 01:23:53,946
<i>The US Ping-Pong team</i>

1068
01:23:53,988 --> 01:23:56,554
<i>met with President Nixon today
at an Oval Office ceremony...</i>

1069
01:23:56,564 --> 01:23:59,118
And wouldn't you know it?
A few months later,

1070
01:23:59,201 --> 01:24:03,164
they invited me and the Ping-Pong team
to visit the White House.

1071
01:24:03,247 --> 01:24:05,499
So, I went, again.

1072
01:24:06,333 --> 01:24:09,795
And I met the President
of the United States, again.

1073
01:24:10,546 --> 01:24:13,507
<i>Only, this time, they didn't get us rooms
in a real fancy hotel.</i>

1074
01:24:13,591 --> 01:24:16,969
<i>So, are you enjoying yourself
in our nation's capital, young man?</i>

1075
01:24:17,053 --> 01:24:20,056
<i>- Yes, sir.
- Well, where are you staying?</i>

1076
01:24:20,139 --> 01:24:22,767
<i>- It's called the Hotel Ebbott.
- Oh, no, no, no, no.</i>

1077
01:24:22,850 --> 01:24:25,978
<i>I know of a much nicer hotel.
It's brand-new, very modern.</i>

1078
01:24:26,062 --> 01:24:28,064
<i>I'll have my people
take care of it for you.</i>

1079
01:24:28,689 --> 01:24:29,815
<i>Security, Frank Wills.</i>

1080
01:24:29,899 --> 01:24:33,486
Yeah, sir, you might want
to send a maintenance man

1081
01:24:33,569 --> 01:24:36,280
over to that office across the way.

1082
01:24:36,322 --> 01:24:39,453
The lights are off, and they must be
looking for a fuse box or something,

1083
01:24:39,463 --> 01:24:41,994
'cause them flashlights,
they're keeping me awake.

1084
01:24:42,078 --> 01:24:43,704
<i>Okay, sir. I'll check it out.</i>

1085
01:24:43,788 --> 01:24:45,498
- Thank you.
<i>- No problem.</i>

1086
01:24:45,581 --> 01:24:47,500
- Good night.
<i>- Good night.</i>

1087
01:24:51,128 --> 01:24:56,509
<i>Therefore, I shall resign the presidency
effective at noon tomorrow.</i>

1088
01:24:56,592 --> 01:24:58,636
<i>Vice President Ford</i>

1089
01:24:58,719 --> 01:25:03,224
<i>will be sworn in as president
at that hour in this office.</i>

1090
01:25:04,600 --> 01:25:09,396
<i>As I recall the high hopes for America
with which we began this second term...</i>

1091
01:25:14,652 --> 01:25:16,195
Sergeant Gump.

1092
01:25:16,695 --> 01:25:18,906
- Yes, sir!
- As you were.

1093
01:25:18,989 --> 01:25:22,118
I have your discharge papers.
Your service is up, son.

1094
01:25:25,538 --> 01:25:28,290
Does this mean
I can't play Ping-Pong no more?

1095
01:25:28,374 --> 01:25:30,334
For the Army it does.

1096
01:25:32,962 --> 01:25:37,842
<i>And just like that, my service
in the United States Army was over.</i>

1097
01:25:43,139 --> 01:25:44,932
<i>So, I went home.</i>

1098
01:26:06,412 --> 01:26:09,832
- I'm home, Mama.
- I know, I know.

1099
01:26:11,458 --> 01:26:13,328
- Louise, he's here.
<i>- Now, when I got home,</i>

1100
01:26:13,338 --> 01:26:17,131
<i>I had no idea,
but Mama had had all sorts of visitors.</i>

1101
01:26:17,256 --> 01:26:19,592
We've had all sorts of visitors, Forrest.

1102
01:26:19,633 --> 01:26:22,761
Everybody wants you
to use their Ping-Pong stuff.

1103
01:26:22,803 --> 01:26:26,599
One man even left a check for $25,000

1104
01:26:26,682 --> 01:26:30,144
if you'd be agreeable to saying
you liked using their paddle.

1105
01:26:30,269 --> 01:26:32,938
Oh, but, Mama,
I only like using my own paddle.

1106
01:26:33,022 --> 01:26:35,024
- Hi, Miss Louise.
- Hey, Forrest.

1107
01:26:35,107 --> 01:26:38,027
I know that. I know that.

1108
01:26:38,110 --> 01:26:40,779
But it's $25,000, Forrest.

1109
01:26:40,863 --> 01:26:45,576
I thought maybe you could hold it
for a while, see if it grows on you.

1110
01:26:45,618 --> 01:26:47,818
- Oh, you look good, Forrest.
<i>- That Mama, she sure was right.</i>

1111
01:26:47,828 --> 01:26:50,331
- You look real good.
<i>- It's funny how things work out.</i>

1112
01:26:50,456 --> 01:26:53,626
<i>I didn't stay home for long,
because I'd made a promise to Bubba,</i>

1113
01:26:53,667 --> 01:26:55,961
<i>and I always try to keep my promise.</i>

1114
01:26:56,003 --> 01:26:57,569
<i>So, I went on down to Bayou La Batre</i>

1115
01:26:57,630 --> 01:27:01,383
<i>to meet Bubba's family
and make their introduction.</i>

1116
01:27:01,467 --> 01:27:05,137
Are you crazy, or just plain stupid?

1117
01:27:05,846 --> 01:27:08,140
Stupid is as stupid does, Mrs. Blue.

1118
01:27:08,182 --> 01:27:09,558
I guess.

1119
01:27:10,559 --> 01:27:14,146
<i>And, of course,
I paid my respect to Bubba himself.</i>

1120
01:27:16,148 --> 01:27:18,692
Hey, Bubba, it's me, Forrest Gump.

1121
01:27:21,820 --> 01:27:25,866
I remember everything you said,
and I got it all figured out.

1122
01:27:28,661 --> 01:27:35,459
I'm taking the $24,562
and 47 cents that I got...

1123
01:27:36,543 --> 01:27:40,172
<i>Or, that's left after a new hair cut
and a new suit,</i>

1124
01:27:40,214 --> 01:27:42,174
<i>and I took Mama out
to a real fancy dinner,</i>

1125
01:27:42,258 --> 01:27:45,511
<i>and I bought a bus ticket
and three Dr. Peppers.</i>

1126
01:27:46,053 --> 01:27:47,846
Tell me something.

1127
01:27:48,889 --> 01:27:51,016
Are you stupid or something?

1128
01:27:51,100 --> 01:27:53,185
Stupid is as stupid does, sir.

1129
01:27:53,227 --> 01:27:56,188
Well, that's what's left after me saying,

1130
01:27:57,062 --> 01:27:59,454
"When I was in China
on the All-America Ping-Pong team,"

1131
01:27:59,464 --> 01:28:03,195
"I just loved playing Ping-Pong with
my Flex-O-Light Ping-Pong paddle,"

1132
01:28:03,237 --> 01:28:04,672
which everybody knows isn't true,

1133
01:28:04,713 --> 01:28:06,540
but Mama says it's just a little white lie

1134
01:28:06,550 --> 01:28:08,577
so it wouldn't hurt nobody.

1135
01:28:09,618 --> 01:28:15,541
So, anyway, I'm putting all that on gas,
ropes and new nets

1136
01:28:16,292 --> 01:28:18,043
and a brand-new shrimping boat.

1137
01:28:39,732 --> 01:28:42,985
<i>Now, Bubba had told me everything
he knew about shrimping,</i>

1138
01:28:43,068 --> 01:28:45,404
<i>but you know what I found out?</i>

1139
01:28:47,072 --> 01:28:49,408
<i>Shrimping is tough.</i>

1140
01:28:51,618 --> 01:28:53,454
I only caught five.

1141
01:28:53,579 --> 01:28:56,915
A couple more,
you could have yourself a cocktail.

1142
01:29:00,252 --> 01:29:02,252
Hey, you ever think
about naming this old boat?

1143
01:29:02,262 --> 01:29:04,932
It's bad luck
to have a boat without a name.

1144
01:29:07,134 --> 01:29:11,972
<i>I'd never named a boat before,
but there was only one I could think of,</i>

1145
01:29:13,140 --> 01:29:16,352
<i>the most beautiful name
in the wide world.</i>

1146
01:29:37,373 --> 01:29:40,209
<i>Now, I hadn't heard from Jenny
in a long while,</i>

1147
01:29:40,292 --> 01:29:42,836
<i>but I thought about her a lot,</i>

1148
01:29:42,961 --> 01:29:46,423
<i>and I hoped that whatever
she was doing made her happy.</i>

1149
01:31:32,696 --> 01:31:35,240
<i>I thought about Jenny all the time.</i>

1150
01:31:59,890 --> 01:32:01,058
Hey!

1151
01:32:24,915 --> 01:32:29,586
Lieutenant Dan, what are you doing here?

1152
01:32:29,670 --> 01:32:33,632
Well, thought I'd try out my sea legs.

1153
01:32:33,674 --> 01:32:37,469
But you ain't got no legs,
Lieutenant Dan.

1154
01:32:37,511 --> 01:32:39,805
Yes, I know that.

1155
01:32:40,138 --> 01:32:42,182
You wrote me a letter, you idiot.

1156
01:32:42,307 --> 01:32:46,853
Well, well. Captain Forrest Gump.
I had to see this for myself.

1157
01:32:48,480 --> 01:32:55,362
And I told you if you were ever
a shrimp boat captain

1158
01:32:55,487 --> 01:32:58,115
that I'd be your first mate.
Well, here I am.

1159
01:32:58,156 --> 01:33:01,326
- I am a man of my word.
- Okay.

1160
01:33:01,368 --> 01:33:05,372
Yeah, but don't you be thinking that
I'm going to be calling you "sir."

1161
01:33:05,497 --> 01:33:06,832
No, sir.

1162
01:33:15,716 --> 01:33:18,010
That's my boat.

1163
01:33:20,596 --> 01:33:26,059
I have a feeling if we head due east,
we'll find some shrimp,

1164
01:33:26,184 --> 01:33:27,769
so take a left.

1165
01:33:29,187 --> 01:33:32,107
- Take a left!
- Which way?

1166
01:33:32,190 --> 01:33:34,860
Over there! They're over there!

1167
01:33:35,527 --> 01:33:39,364
- Get on the wheel and take a left!
- Okay.

1168
01:33:40,574 --> 01:33:44,703
Gump, what are you doing?
Take a left! Left!

1169
01:33:47,080 --> 01:33:50,709
That's where we're going
to find those shrimp, my boy!

1170
01:33:52,294 --> 01:33:53,879
That's where we'll find them.

1171
01:34:06,558 --> 01:34:10,687
- Still no shrimp, Lieutenant Dan.
- Okay, so I was wrong.

1172
01:34:11,396 --> 01:34:14,608
How are we going to find them?

1173
01:34:14,733 --> 01:34:17,235
Well, maybe you should
just pray for shrimp.

1174
01:34:23,867 --> 01:34:26,536
<i>So, I went to church every Sunday.</i>

1175
01:34:27,788 --> 01:34:29,790
<i>Sometimes Lieutenant Dan came, too,</i>

1176
01:34:29,915 --> 01:34:32,918
<i>though I think
he left the praying up to me.</i>

1177
01:34:48,392 --> 01:34:52,771
- No shrimp.
- Where the hell's this God of yours?

1178
01:34:53,605 --> 01:34:59,319
<i>It's funny Lieutenant Dan said that,
'cause right then, God showed up.</i>

1179
01:35:16,169 --> 01:35:21,007
- You'll never sink this boat!
<i>- Now, me, I was scared,</i>

1180
01:35:21,133 --> 01:35:24,177
<i>but Lieutenant Dan, he was mad.</i>

1181
01:35:24,302 --> 01:35:25,637
Come on!

1182
01:35:28,765 --> 01:35:33,979
You call this a storm?
Come on, you son of a bitch!

1183
01:35:36,106 --> 01:35:40,485
It's time for a showdown! You and me!

1184
01:35:40,610 --> 01:35:44,489
I'm right here! Come and get me!

1185
01:35:46,283 --> 01:35:50,162
You'll never sink this boat!

1186
01:35:52,205 --> 01:35:54,374
<i>Hurricane Carmen
came through here yesterday,</i>

1187
01:35:54,499 --> 01:35:57,043
<i>destroying nearly everything in its path.</i>

1188
01:35:57,169 --> 01:35:59,671
<i>And as in other towns
up and down the coast,</i>

1189
01:35:59,838 --> 01:36:02,215
<i>Bayou La Batre's
entire shrimping industry</i>

1190
01:36:02,299 --> 01:36:06,178
<i>has fallen victim to Carmen
and has been left in utter ruin.</i>

1191
01:36:06,303 --> 01:36:09,473
<i>Speaking with local officials,
this reporter has learned,</i>

1192
01:36:09,514 --> 01:36:12,976
<i>in fact, only one shrimping boat
actually survived the storm.</i>

1193
01:36:13,351 --> 01:36:15,979
Louise. Louise, there's Forrest.

1194
01:36:16,688 --> 01:36:18,690
<i>After that, shrimping was easy.</i>

1195
01:36:24,362 --> 01:36:27,532
<i>Since people still needed
them shrimps for shrimp cocktails</i>

1196
01:36:27,574 --> 01:36:31,703
and barbecues and all,
and we were the only boat left standing,

1197
01:36:31,870 --> 01:36:35,165
Bubba-Gump Shrimp's what they got.

1198
01:36:35,207 --> 01:36:39,836
We got a whole bunch of boats, 12 <i>Jennys,</i>

1199
01:36:39,878 --> 01:36:43,381
a big old warehouse. We even have
hats that say "Bubba-Gump" on them.

1200
01:36:43,715 --> 01:36:47,010
Bubba-Gump Shrimp. It's a household name.

1201
01:36:47,219 --> 01:36:48,929
Hold on there, boy.

1202
01:36:49,054 --> 01:36:53,600
Are you telling me you're the owner of
the Bubba-Gump Shrimp Corporation?

1203
01:36:53,725 --> 01:36:56,728
Yes, sir. We got more money
than Davy Crockett.

1204
01:36:58,355 --> 01:37:02,400
Boy, I heard some whoppers in my time,
but that tops them all.

1205
01:37:05,111 --> 01:37:07,906
We was sitting next to a millionaire.

1206
01:37:11,409 --> 01:37:16,039
Well, I thought it was
a very lovely story,

1207
01:37:16,456 --> 01:37:21,086
and you tell it so well,
with such enthusiasm.

1208
01:37:22,796 --> 01:37:25,465
Would you like to see
what Lieutenant Dan looks like?

1209
01:37:25,590 --> 01:37:27,092
Well, yes, I would.

1210
01:37:32,305 --> 01:37:34,349
That's him right there.

1211
01:37:36,476 --> 01:37:38,737
And let me tell you something
about Lieutenant Dan...

1212
01:37:39,896 --> 01:37:40,939
Forrest,

1213
01:37:46,486 --> 01:37:49,281
I never thanked you for saving my life.

1214
01:38:15,307 --> 01:38:21,605
<i>He never actually said so,
but I think he made his peace with God.</i>

1215
01:38:29,279 --> 01:38:31,489
<i>For the second time in 17 days,</i>

1216
01:38:31,615 --> 01:38:35,076
<i>President Ford escaped
possible assassination today.</i>

1217
01:38:35,160 --> 01:38:36,494
<i>Base to</i> Jenny 1.

1218
01:38:36,536 --> 01:38:40,040
<i>- Base to</i> Jenny 1.
<i>- Jenny 1</i>. Go, Margo.

1219
01:38:40,123 --> 01:38:41,666
<i>Forrest has a phone call.</i>

1220
01:38:41,708 --> 01:38:44,210
Yeah, well, you'll have to tell them
to call him back.

1221
01:38:44,294 --> 01:38:47,672
- He is indisposed at the moment.
<i>- His mama's sick.</i>

1222
01:39:08,360 --> 01:39:10,737
- Where's Mama?
- She's upstairs.

1223
01:39:13,573 --> 01:39:15,533
Hi, Forrest.

1224
01:39:16,493 --> 01:39:19,037
- I'll see you tomorrow.
- All right.

1225
01:39:25,710 --> 01:39:28,880
We sure got you straightened out,
didn't we, boy?

1226
01:39:40,225 --> 01:39:44,187
- What's the matter, Mama?
- I'm dying, Forrest.

1227
01:39:47,524 --> 01:39:49,901
Come on in, sit down over here.

1228
01:40:04,249 --> 01:40:07,752
- Why are you dying, Mama?
- It's my time.

1229
01:40:08,753 --> 01:40:10,630
It's just my time.

1230
01:40:12,090 --> 01:40:16,261
Now, don't you be afraid, sweetheart.

1231
01:40:17,887 --> 01:40:20,265
Death is just a part of life,

1232
01:40:21,266 --> 01:40:23,893
something we're all destined to do.

1233
01:40:25,729 --> 01:40:30,108
I didn't know it,
but I was destined to be your mama.

1234
01:40:30,942 --> 01:40:34,529
- I did the best I could.
- You did good, Mama.

1235
01:40:35,321 --> 01:40:40,493
Well, I happen to believe
you make your own destiny.

1236
01:40:41,995 --> 01:40:45,248
You have to do the best
with what God gave you.

1237
01:40:49,127 --> 01:40:51,254
What's my destiny, Mama?

1238
01:40:53,423 --> 01:40:56,634
You're going to have
to figure that out for yourself.

1239
01:40:57,927 --> 01:41:00,930
Life is a box of chocolates, Forrest.

1240
01:41:00,972 --> 01:41:03,141
You never know what you're going to get.

1241
01:41:03,266 --> 01:41:07,645
<i>Mama always had a way of explaining
things so I could understand them.</i>

1242
01:41:07,729 --> 01:41:09,939
I will miss you, Forrest.

1243
01:41:11,775 --> 01:41:15,820
<i>She had got the cancer
and died on a Tuesday.</i>

1244
01:41:17,322 --> 01:41:20,658
<i>I bought her a new hat
with little flowers on it.</i>

1245
01:41:23,703 --> 01:41:26,998
And that's all I have to say about that.

1246
01:41:33,838 --> 01:41:36,273
Didn't you say you were waiting
for the number seven bus?

1247
01:41:36,283 --> 01:41:39,077
There'll be another one along shortly.

1248
01:41:42,847 --> 01:41:46,476
Now, because I had been a football star,
and a war hero,

1249
01:41:46,518 --> 01:41:49,646
and a national celebrity,
and a shrimping boat captain,

1250
01:41:50,146 --> 01:41:53,358
and a college graduate,
the city fathers of Greenbow, Alabama

1251
01:41:53,483 --> 01:41:56,694
decided to get together
and offered me a fine job.

1252
01:41:58,071 --> 01:42:01,741
<i>So, I never went back to work
for Lieutenant Dan,</i>

1253
01:42:01,866 --> 01:42:04,577
<i>though he did take care
of my Bubba-Gump money.</i>

1254
01:42:04,702 --> 01:42:09,332
<i>He got me invested
in some kind of fruit company.</i>

1255
01:42:09,374 --> 01:42:11,157
<i>And so then, I got a call from him saying</i>

1256
01:42:11,167 --> 01:42:14,546
we don't have to worry about money
no more, and I said,

1257
01:42:14,587 --> 01:42:16,881
"That's good. One less thing."

1258
01:42:19,926 --> 01:42:23,304
<i>Now, Mama said there's only
so much fortune a man really needs,</i>

1259
01:42:24,556 --> 01:42:27,433
<i>and the rest is just for showing off.</i>

1260
01:42:27,517 --> 01:42:31,396
<i>So, I gave a whole bunch of it
to the Foursquare gospel church,</i>

1261
01:42:34,065 --> 01:42:38,570
<i>and I gave a whole bunch to the
Bayou La Batre fishing hospital.</i>

1262
01:42:40,905 --> 01:42:45,451
<i>And even though Bubba was dead
and Lieutenant Dan said I was nuts,</i>

1263
01:42:45,577 --> 01:42:48,204
<i>I gave Bubba's mama Bubba's share.</i>

1264
01:42:52,417 --> 01:42:54,127
You know what?

1265
01:42:55,378 --> 01:42:58,423
<i>She didn't have to work
in nobody's kitchen no more.</i>

1266
01:42:58,464 --> 01:43:00,091
That smells wonderful.

1267
01:43:00,925 --> 01:43:04,888
<i>And 'cause I was a gazillionaire
and I liked doing it so much,</i>

1268
01:43:04,929 --> 01:43:07,265
<i>I cut that grass for free.</i>

1269
01:43:11,060 --> 01:43:13,938
<i>But at night time
when there was nothing to do</i>

1270
01:43:14,022 --> 01:43:16,399
<i>and the house was all empty,</i>

1271
01:43:17,400 --> 01:43:19,777
<i>I'd always think of Jenny.</i>

1272
01:44:23,466 --> 01:44:26,636
<i>And then, she was there.</i>

1273
01:44:59,627 --> 01:45:02,797
- Hello, Forrest.
- Hello, Jenny.

1274
01:45:14,350 --> 01:45:16,978
<i>Jenny came back and stayed with me.</i>

1275
01:45:18,563 --> 01:45:22,233
<i>Maybe it was because
she had nowhere else to go,</i>

1276
01:45:22,358 --> 01:45:26,070
<i>or maybe it was because she was
so tired, 'cause she went to bed</i>

1277
01:45:26,195 --> 01:45:30,158
<i>and slept and slept,
like she hadn't slept in years.</i>

1278
01:45:31,409 --> 01:45:33,703
<i>It was wonderful having her home.</i>

1279
01:45:35,038 --> 01:45:40,209
<i>Every day we'd take a walk and
I'd jabber on like a monkey in a tree,</i>

1280
01:45:40,251 --> 01:45:42,795
<i>and she'd listen about Ping-Ponging,
and shrimping,</i>

1281
01:45:42,879 --> 01:45:47,216
<i>and Mama making a trip up to heaven.
I did all the talking.</i>

1282
01:45:47,258 --> 01:45:50,595
<i>Jenny most of the time was real quiet.</i>

1283
01:46:30,760 --> 01:46:33,971
How could you do this?

1284
01:47:10,925 --> 01:47:14,262
<i>Sometimes I guess there
just aren't enough rocks.</i>

1285
01:47:16,472 --> 01:47:20,977
<i>I never really knew why she came back,
but I didn't care.</i>

1286
01:47:21,144 --> 01:47:25,440
<i>It was like olden times.
We was like peas and carrots again.</i>

1287
01:47:27,525 --> 01:47:31,863
<i>Every day, I'd pick pretty flowers
and put them in her room for her,</i>

1288
01:47:33,364 --> 01:47:36,993
<i>and she gave me the best gift anyone
could ever get in the wide world.</i>

1289
01:47:37,034 --> 01:47:39,871
- New shoes.
- They make them just for running.

1290
01:47:44,876 --> 01:47:48,171
<i>And she even showed me how to dance.</i>

1291
01:47:56,345 --> 01:48:00,558
<i>And, well, we was like family,
Jenny and me.</i>

1292
01:48:04,312 --> 01:48:07,231
<i>And it was the happiest time in my life.</i>

1293
01:48:26,876 --> 01:48:28,703
<i>...and this Fourth is witnessing
one of the</i>

1294
01:48:28,753 --> 01:48:31,756
<i>largest fireworks displays
in the nation's...</i>

1295
01:48:31,839 --> 01:48:34,759
- You done watching it?
<i>- ...here in New York Harbor...</i>

1296
01:48:34,884 --> 01:48:37,058
- I'm going to bed.
<i>- ...with a spectacular display</i>

1297
01:48:37,068 --> 01:48:40,112
<i>of tall ships earlier.
The Statue of Liberty...</i>

1298
01:48:46,854 --> 01:48:48,856
Will you marry me?

1299
01:48:53,778 --> 01:48:56,739
I'd make a good husband, Jenny.

1300
01:48:59,408 --> 01:49:01,452
You would, Forrest.

1301
01:49:03,287 --> 01:49:05,623
But you won't marry me.

1302
01:49:07,917 --> 01:49:10,127
You don't want to marry me.

1303
01:49:13,714 --> 01:49:16,133
Why don't you love me, Jenny?

1304
01:49:21,138 --> 01:49:23,266
I'm not a smart man,

1305
01:49:24,976 --> 01:49:27,395
but I know what love is.

1306
01:50:04,432 --> 01:50:05,683
Jenny.

1307
01:50:07,602 --> 01:50:10,104
Forrest, I do love you.

1308
01:51:03,240 --> 01:51:06,911
- Where are you running off to?
- I'm not running.

1309
01:52:38,502 --> 01:52:43,841
<i>That day, for no particular reason,
I decided to go for a little run.</i>

1310
01:52:45,009 --> 01:52:49,430
<i>So, I ran to the end of the road,
and when I got there,</i>

1311
01:52:49,513 --> 01:52:51,340
<i>I thought maybe I'd run
to the end of town.</i>

1312
01:52:51,350 --> 01:52:54,602
<i>President Carter, suffering from heat
exhaustion, fell into the arms of...</i>

1313
01:52:54,685 --> 01:52:56,353
<i>And when I got there,</i>

1314
01:52:56,437 --> 01:53:00,608
<i>I thought maybe I'd just
run across Greenbow County.</i>

1315
01:53:00,691 --> 01:53:03,110
<i>And I figured since I'd run this far,</i>

1316
01:53:03,194 --> 01:53:06,489
<i>maybe I'd just run across
the great state of Alabama.</i>

1317
01:53:06,530 --> 01:53:07,740
<i>And that's what I did.</i>

1318
01:53:08,365 --> 01:53:10,159
I ran clear across Alabama.

1319
01:53:11,202 --> 01:53:14,371
For no particular reason,
I just kept on going.

1320
01:53:15,706 --> 01:53:17,291
I ran clear to the ocean.

1321
01:53:23,172 --> 01:53:26,342
<i>And when I got there,
I figured since I'd gone this far,</i>

1322
01:53:26,884 --> 01:53:29,720
<i>might as well turn around
and just keep on going.</i>

1323
01:53:33,474 --> 01:53:38,062
<i>And when I got to another ocean,
I figured since I'd gone this far,</i>

1324
01:53:39,855 --> 01:53:43,567
<i>I might as well just turn back
and keep right on going.</i>

1325
01:53:44,735 --> 01:53:49,573
<i>When I got tired, I slept.
When I got hungry, I ate.</i>

1326
01:53:49,657 --> 01:53:52,701
When I had to go, you know...

1327
01:53:54,328 --> 01:53:55,538
I went.

1328
01:53:55,579 --> 01:53:58,582
And so, you just ran.

1329
01:54:00,334 --> 01:54:01,418
Yeah.

1330
01:54:36,704 --> 01:54:41,959
<i>I'd think a lot about Mama
and Bubba and Lieutenant Dan.</i>

1331
01:54:42,960 --> 01:54:46,463
<i>But most of all, I thought about Jenny.</i>

1332
01:54:47,548 --> 01:54:49,717
<i>I thought about her a lot.</i>

1333
01:54:50,467 --> 01:54:53,596
<i>For more than two years now,
a man named Forrest Gump,</i>

1334
01:54:53,637 --> 01:54:57,057
<i>a gardener from Greenbow, Alabama,
stopping only to sleep,</i>

1335
01:54:57,141 --> 01:54:59,310
<i>has been running across America.</i>

1336
01:54:59,393 --> 01:55:01,395
<i>Charles Cooper brings us this report.</i>

1337
01:55:02,313 --> 01:55:04,732
<i>For the fourth time
on his journey across America,</i>

1338
01:55:04,815 --> 01:55:07,651
<i>Forrest Gump,
the gardener from Greenbow, Alabama,</i>

1339
01:55:07,776 --> 01:55:10,654
<i>is about to cross
the Mississippi River again today.</i>

1340
01:55:11,280 --> 01:55:13,585
- I'll be damned. Forrest?
<i>- Sir, why are you running?</i>

1341
01:55:13,595 --> 01:55:14,491
Why are you running?

1342
01:55:14,575 --> 01:55:16,160
Are you doing this for world peace?

1343
01:55:16,243 --> 01:55:17,809
Are you doing this for the homeless?

1344
01:55:17,819 --> 01:55:20,664
- Are you running for women's rights?
- Or for the environment?

1345
01:55:20,748 --> 01:55:21,790
Or for animals?

1346
01:55:21,832 --> 01:55:24,752
<i>They just couldn't believe that
somebody would do all that running</i>

1347
01:55:24,835 --> 01:55:26,211
<i>for no particular reason.</i>

1348
01:55:26,295 --> 01:55:28,297
Why are you doing this?

1349
01:55:28,339 --> 01:55:30,841
I just felt like running.

1350
01:55:30,966 --> 01:55:33,344
I just felt like running.

1351
01:55:33,469 --> 01:55:36,680
It's you. I can't believe it's really you.

1352
01:55:37,514 --> 01:55:42,645
Now, for some reason, what I was doing
seemed to make sense to people.

1353
01:55:42,811 --> 01:55:45,012
I mean, it was like an alarm
went off in my head, you know?

1354
01:55:45,022 --> 01:55:47,153
I said,
"Here's a guy that's got his act together.

1355
01:55:47,278 --> 01:55:49,280
"Here's somebody
who's got it all figured out.

1356
01:55:49,322 --> 01:55:53,155
"Here's somebody who has the answer."
I'll follow you anywhere, Mr. Gump.

1357
01:55:53,197 --> 01:55:55,032
<i>So, I got company.</i>

1358
01:55:56,867 --> 01:56:02,706
<i>And after that, I got more company.
And then, even more people joined in.</i>

1359
01:56:05,167 --> 01:56:08,379
Somebody later told me
it gave people hope.

1360
01:56:10,172 --> 01:56:13,550
Now... Now, I don't know
anything about that,

1361
01:56:14,385 --> 01:56:16,971
<i>but some of those people
asked me if I could help them out.</i>

1362
01:56:17,179 --> 01:56:20,432
Hey, man, hey, listen, I was wondering
if you might help me, huh?

1363
01:56:20,516 --> 01:56:22,299
Listen, I'm in the
bumper sticker business

1364
01:56:22,351 --> 01:56:24,176
and I've been trying
to think up a good slogan.

1365
01:56:24,186 --> 01:56:27,317
And since you have been such a big
inspiration to the people around here,

1366
01:56:27,398 --> 01:56:29,572
I thought you might
be able to help me jump into...

1367
01:56:29,582 --> 01:56:33,210
Whoa, man! You just ran through
a big pile of dog shit!

1368
01:56:34,571 --> 01:56:37,241
- It happens.
- What, shit?

1369
01:56:38,742 --> 01:56:40,703
Sometimes.

1370
01:56:42,579 --> 01:56:45,249
<i>And some years later,
I heard that that fellow</i>

1371
01:56:45,289 --> 01:56:47,072
<i>did come up with a bumper sticker slogan,</i>

1372
01:56:47,082 --> 01:56:50,294
<i>and he made a lot of money off of it.</i>

1373
01:56:51,714 --> 01:56:53,924
<i>Another time, I was running along,</i>

1374
01:56:54,049 --> 01:56:57,386
<i>somebody who had lost all his money
in the T-shirt business,</i>

1375
01:56:57,428 --> 01:56:59,471
<i>he wanted to put my face on a T-shirt,</i>

1376
01:56:59,555 --> 01:57:02,558
<i>but he couldn't draw that well,
and he didn't have a camera.</i>

1377
01:57:02,599 --> 01:57:06,103
Here, use this one.
Nobody likes that color anyway.

1378
01:57:10,941 --> 01:57:12,609
Have a nice day.

1379
01:57:14,236 --> 01:57:15,362
<i>Well, some years later,</i>

1380
01:57:15,446 --> 01:57:19,366
<i>I found out that that man
did come up with an idea for a T-shirt.</i>

1381
01:57:19,450 --> 01:57:21,827
<i>He made a lot of money off of it.</i>

1382
01:57:24,621 --> 01:57:29,043
<i>Anyway, like I was saying,
I had a lot of company.</i>

1383
01:57:30,294 --> 01:57:31,462
<i>My mama always said,</i>

1384
01:57:31,545 --> 01:57:35,966
<i>"You got to put the past behind you
before you can move on."</i>

1385
01:57:37,634 --> 01:57:40,971
<i>And I think that's what
my running was all about.</i>

1386
01:57:41,805 --> 01:57:45,809
<i>I had run for three years, two months,</i>

1387
01:57:46,060 --> 01:57:48,395
<i>14 days and 16 hours.</i>

1388
01:58:04,078 --> 01:58:06,413
Quiet. Quiet.
He's going to say something.

1389
01:58:17,841 --> 01:58:19,593
I'm pretty tired.

1390
01:58:22,429 --> 01:58:24,473
Think I'll go home now.

1391
01:58:43,033 --> 01:58:45,494
Now what are we supposed to do?

1392
01:58:46,453 --> 01:58:50,707
<i>And just like that,
my running days was over.</i>

1393
01:58:52,668 --> 01:58:54,419
<i>So, I went home to Alabama.</i>

1394
01:58:55,212 --> 01:58:59,383
<i>Moments ago, at 2:25 p.m.,
as President Reagan was leaving the...</i>

1395
01:59:01,135 --> 01:59:05,305
<i>...five or six gunshots were fired
by an unknown would-be assassin.</i>

1396
01:59:05,806 --> 01:59:08,241
<i>The President was shot in the chest,
and the assailant...</i>

1397
01:59:08,251 --> 01:59:10,211
I picked up the mail.

1398
01:59:10,978 --> 01:59:14,857
And one day, out of the blue clear sky,
I got a letter from Jenny,

1399
01:59:14,898 --> 01:59:19,194
wondering if I could come down
to Savannah and see her,

1400
01:59:19,236 --> 01:59:21,822
and that's what I'm doing here.

1401
01:59:21,905 --> 01:59:24,533
She saw me on TV, running.

1402
01:59:24,575 --> 01:59:28,829
I'm supposed to go on the
number nine bus to Richmond Street

1403
01:59:28,912 --> 01:59:35,836
and get off and go one block left
to 1947 Henry Street, Apartment 4.

1404
01:59:35,919 --> 01:59:39,590
Why, you don't need to take a bus.

1405
01:59:39,715 --> 01:59:44,261
Henry Street is just five
or six blocks down that way.

1406
01:59:46,096 --> 01:59:48,432
- Down that way?
- Down that way.

1407
01:59:51,435 --> 01:59:53,353
It was nice talking to you.

1408
01:59:54,396 --> 01:59:57,024
I hope everything works out for you!

1409
02:00:04,781 --> 02:00:06,450
Hey!

1410
02:00:06,867 --> 02:00:08,535
Forrest!

1411
02:00:08,785 --> 02:00:12,039
How you doing? Come in, come in!

1412
02:00:12,122 --> 02:00:13,332
I got your letter.

1413
02:00:13,415 --> 02:00:16,043
I was wondering about that.

1414
02:00:17,586 --> 02:00:19,421
Is this your house?

1415
02:00:19,463 --> 02:00:22,549
Yeah. It's messy right now.
I just got off work.

1416
02:00:22,633 --> 02:00:26,345
It's nice. You got air conditioning.

1417
02:00:33,227 --> 02:00:35,270
- Thank you.
- I ate some.

1418
02:00:38,065 --> 02:00:43,487
Hey, I kept a scrapbook
of your clippings and everything.

1419
02:00:43,612 --> 02:00:45,239
There you are.

1420
02:00:46,990 --> 02:00:48,208
And this, I got you running.

1421
02:00:51,161 --> 02:00:53,330
I ran a long way,

1422
02:00:53,830 --> 02:00:55,666
for a long time.

1423
02:00:57,876 --> 02:00:59,378
And there...

1424
02:01:05,884 --> 02:01:09,346
Listen, Forrest,
I don't know how to say this.

1425
02:01:11,848 --> 02:01:16,186
I just I want to apologize
for anything that I ever did to you,

1426
02:01:16,311 --> 02:01:21,566
'cause I was messed up
for a long time, and...

1427
02:01:24,361 --> 02:01:25,988
- Hey.
- Hi.

1428
02:01:26,196 --> 02:01:27,197
Hey, you.

1429
02:01:28,365 --> 02:01:31,368
- This is an old friend from Alabama.
- How do you do?

1430
02:01:31,410 --> 02:01:34,584
Listen, next week my schedule changes,
so I'll be able to... But thanks...

1431
02:01:34,594 --> 02:01:36,638
No problem. Got to go, Jen,
I'm double-parked.

1432
02:01:36,707 --> 02:01:38,583
- Okay. Thanks.
- Bye.

1433
02:01:42,045 --> 02:01:44,840
This is my very good friend, Mr. Gump.
Can you say hi to him?

1434
02:01:44,881 --> 02:01:48,010
- Hello, Mr. Gump.
- Hello.

1435
02:01:48,051 --> 02:01:51,054
- Can I go watch TV now?
- Yes, you can. Just keep it low.

1436
02:01:53,890 --> 02:01:57,227
- You're a mama, Jenny.
- I'm a mama.

1437
02:02:00,105 --> 02:02:01,940
His name's Forrest.

1438
02:02:03,066 --> 02:02:04,401
Like me.

1439
02:02:06,028 --> 02:02:08,155
I named him after his daddy.

1440
02:02:09,114 --> 02:02:11,575
He got a daddy named Forrest, too?

1441
02:02:12,868 --> 02:02:14,911
You're his daddy, Forrest.

1442
02:02:29,384 --> 02:02:30,594
Hey.

1443
02:02:31,762 --> 02:02:34,639
Forrest, look at me. Look at me, Forrest.

1444
02:02:37,225 --> 02:02:41,355
There's nothing you need to do, okay?
You didn't do anything wrong.

1445
02:02:41,897 --> 02:02:43,273
Okay?

1446
02:02:47,611 --> 02:02:49,488
Isn't he beautiful?

1447
02:02:50,489 --> 02:02:53,450
He's the most beautiful thing
I've ever seen.

1448
02:02:57,245 --> 02:02:58,330
But...

1449
02:03:02,000 --> 02:03:04,920
Is he smart, or...

1450
02:03:04,961 --> 02:03:08,965
He's very smart.
He's one of the smartest in his class.

1451
02:03:18,308 --> 02:03:20,769
Yeah, it's okay. Go talk to him.

1452
02:03:30,112 --> 02:03:32,948
- What are you watching?
- Bert and Ernie.

1453
02:03:56,054 --> 02:03:57,848
Forrest,

1454
02:03:59,307 --> 02:04:00,851
I'm sick.

1455
02:04:03,520 --> 02:04:07,190
What, do you have a cough due to a cold?

1456
02:04:07,232 --> 02:04:09,651
I have some kind of virus,

1457
02:04:09,693 --> 02:04:12,404
and the doctors don't...
They don't know what it is,

1458
02:04:12,529 --> 02:04:15,532
and there isn't anything
they can do about it.

1459
02:04:19,911 --> 02:04:22,205
You could come home with me.

1460
02:04:23,874 --> 02:04:29,546
Jenny, you and little Forrest could
come stay at my house in Greenbow.

1461
02:04:33,884 --> 02:04:36,678
I'll take care of you if you're sick.

1462
02:04:39,055 --> 02:04:41,349
Would you marry me, Forrest?

1463
02:04:46,605 --> 02:04:47,856
Okay.

1464
02:04:48,899 --> 02:04:50,567
Please take your seats.

1465
02:04:54,404 --> 02:04:56,740
Forrest? It's time to start.

1466
02:05:16,134 --> 02:05:17,719
Hi.

1467
02:05:18,595 --> 02:05:20,096
Your tie.

1468
02:05:32,651 --> 02:05:34,277
Lieutenant Dan.

1469
02:05:49,626 --> 02:05:51,586
Lieutenant Dan.

1470
02:05:52,420 --> 02:05:54,089
Hello, Forrest.

1471
02:05:54,756 --> 02:05:57,425
You got new legs. New legs!

1472
02:05:58,635 --> 02:06:02,430
Yeah. I got new legs. Custom-made.

1473
02:06:03,139 --> 02:06:07,143
Titanium alloy.
It's what they use on the space shuttle.

1474
02:06:10,981 --> 02:06:12,482
Magic legs.

1475
02:06:14,484 --> 02:06:18,863
This is my fiancée, Susan.

1476
02:06:21,658 --> 02:06:25,036
- Lieutenant Dan.
- Hi, Forrest.

1477
02:06:27,122 --> 02:06:30,333
Lieutenant Dan, this is my Jenny.

1478
02:06:30,709 --> 02:06:33,712
Hey. It's nice to meet you finally.

1479
02:06:43,847 --> 02:06:48,018
Do you, Forrest,
take Jenny to be your wife?

1480
02:06:49,894 --> 02:06:54,149
Do you, Jenny,
take Forrest to be your husband?

1481
02:06:55,483 --> 02:06:58,862
And so I pronounce you man and wife.

1482
02:07:29,726 --> 02:07:31,603
- Hey.
- Hey.

1483
02:07:45,283 --> 02:07:47,077
Hey, Forrest.

1484
02:07:52,415 --> 02:07:54,209
Were you scared in Vietnam?

1485
02:07:55,877 --> 02:07:58,213
Yes. Well, I...

1486
02:07:59,547 --> 02:08:01,257
I don't know.

1487
02:08:01,966 --> 02:08:06,930
<i>Sometimes it would stop raining long
enough for the stars to come out.</i>

1488
02:08:10,058 --> 02:08:12,102
<i>And then it was nice.</i>

1489
02:08:15,480 --> 02:08:19,442
It was like just before the sun
goes to bed down on the bayou.

1490
02:08:20,735 --> 02:08:24,614
<i>There was always
a million sparkles on the water.</i>

1491
02:08:26,408 --> 02:08:30,328
<i>Like that mountain lake.
It was so clear, Jenny,</i>

1492
02:08:30,453 --> 02:08:35,041
<i>it looked like there were two skies,
one on top of the other.</i>

1493
02:08:37,585 --> 02:08:40,630
And then, in the desert,
when the sun comes up,

1494
02:08:43,091 --> 02:08:47,262
<i>I couldn't tell where heaven stopped</i>

1495
02:08:47,804 --> 02:08:50,181
<i>and the earth began.</i>

1496
02:08:51,433 --> 02:08:53,309
<i>It was so beautiful.</i>

1497
02:08:58,022 --> 02:09:01,109
I wish I could've been there with you.

1498
02:09:04,195 --> 02:09:05,613
You were.

1499
02:09:16,332 --> 02:09:17,792
I love you.

1500
02:09:22,172 --> 02:09:25,508
<i>You died on a Saturday morning.</i>

1501
02:09:27,218 --> 02:09:30,972
And I had you placed here under our tree.

1502
02:09:35,852 --> 02:09:40,690
And I had that house of your father's
bulldozed to the ground.

1503
02:09:44,819 --> 02:09:46,488
<i>Mama</i>

1504
02:09:47,572 --> 02:09:52,577
always said that dying was a part of life.

1505
02:09:55,997 --> 02:09:58,333
I sure wish it wasn't.

1506
02:10:01,002 --> 02:10:04,756
Little Forrest is doing just fine.

1507
02:10:06,090 --> 02:10:07,175
But...

1508
02:10:07,425 --> 02:10:10,094
<i>About to start school again soon,</i>

1509
02:10:11,930 --> 02:10:15,725
and I make his breakfast, lunch
and dinner every day.

1510
02:10:17,894 --> 02:10:23,900
I make sure he combs his hair
and brushes his teeth every day.

1511
02:10:27,028 --> 02:10:29,614
Teaching him how to play Ping-Pong.

1512
02:10:30,907 --> 02:10:31,950
Okay.

1513
02:10:32,200 --> 02:10:33,409
<i>He's really good.</i>

1514
02:10:33,451 --> 02:10:35,578
Forrest, you go.

1515
02:10:39,791 --> 02:10:41,376
<i>We fish a lot.</i>

1516
02:10:44,921 --> 02:10:48,383
And every night, we read a book.
He's so smart, Jenny.

1517
02:10:51,636 --> 02:10:53,888
You'd be so proud of him.

1518
02:10:55,598 --> 02:10:57,058
I am.

1519
02:10:58,101 --> 02:11:01,312
He wrote you a letter.

1520
02:11:02,897 --> 02:11:04,941
And he says I can't read it.

1521
02:11:05,066 --> 02:11:08,611
I'm not supposed to,
so I'll just leave it here for you.

1522
02:11:24,669 --> 02:11:26,004
Jenny,

1523
02:11:31,801 --> 02:11:35,013
I don't know if Mama was right,

1524
02:11:36,347 --> 02:11:37,849
or if it's Lieutenant Dan.

1525
02:11:37,974 --> 02:11:40,602
I don't know

1526
02:11:40,643 --> 02:11:45,148
if we each have a destiny,

1527
02:11:47,191 --> 02:11:52,322
or if we're all just floating around
accidental-like on a breeze.

1528
02:11:56,826 --> 02:11:58,661
But I think

1529
02:12:00,538 --> 02:12:02,332
maybe it's both.

1530
02:12:06,669 --> 02:12:09,547
Maybe both is happening at the same time.

1531
02:12:15,678 --> 02:12:17,680
But I miss you, Jenny.

1532
02:12:24,062 --> 02:12:28,483
If there's anything you need,
I won't be far away.

1533
02:13:03,768 --> 02:13:06,729
Here's your bus. Okay.

1534
02:13:08,398 --> 02:13:11,734
Hey. I know this.

1535
02:13:11,859 --> 02:13:14,737
I'm gonna show that
for show-and-tell because

1536
02:13:14,862 --> 02:13:17,573
Grandma used to read it to you.

1537
02:13:17,615 --> 02:13:19,742
My favorite book.

1538
02:13:23,079 --> 02:13:24,580
Here we are.

1539
02:13:24,747 --> 02:13:26,207
Okay.

1540
02:13:27,917 --> 02:13:29,419
Here you go.

1541
02:13:34,298 --> 02:13:36,801
Hey, Forrest, don't...

1542
02:13:40,263 --> 02:13:43,975
- I wanted to tell you, I love you.
- I love you, too, Daddy.

1543
02:13:45,977 --> 02:13:48,771
I'll be right here when you get back.

1544
02:13:53,317 --> 02:13:56,612
You understand this is
the bus to school, now, don't you?

1545
02:13:56,654 --> 02:14:00,199
Of course, and you are Dorothy Harris,
and I'm Forrest Gump.

